## Why This Is Asked
Real-world systems demand ultra-low latency allocations with NUMA awareness. A per-core cache reduces cross-socket traffic; a lock-free global pool avoids stalls under high contention; tagged pointers prevent ABA without heavy marshaling.

## Key Concepts
- Per-core caches and local allocation path
- Lock-free free lists with ABA avoidance via pointer tagging
- Cross-socket NUMA considerations and cache-line alignment
- Reclamation strategy to minimize fragmentation and stalls

## Code Example
```javascript
// alloc (pseudo)
function alloc(core) {
  if (core.local.head) { return pop(core.local); }
  refillFromGlobal(core);
  return pop(core.local);
}

function free(core, block) {
  push(core.local, block);
  // if local full, push to global refcounted pool
}
```

