## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design lock-free, NUMA-friendly timeouts with tight latency budgets and predictable memory access patterns. The answer demonstrates practical trade-offs between per-core locality and a minimal global coordination path.

## Key Concepts
- Lock-free data structures and ABA avoidance
- Per-core timer buckets and cache-line alignment
- Two-tier timer wheels for short vs long timeouts
- Safe cancellation via id-to-timer mapping and sequence counters
- Crash-safe recovery implications (logs, id replay)

## Code Example
