## Why This Is Asked

Tests understanding of safe, non-blocking reclamation in a shared object graph, balancing hazard pointers with epoch-based techniques. The scenario emphasizes NUMA locality and cross-thread safety, common in database-like systems.

## Key Concepts

- Hazard pointers
- Epoch-based reclamation
- Per-thread fast paths
- Memory ordering and fences
- NUMA considerations

## Code Example

```c
typedef struct Obj {
  atomic_uint refcount;
  atomic_uint epoch;
  struct Obj* next;
} Obj;

void pin(Obj* o) { atomic_fetch_add_explicit(&o->refcount, 1, memory_order_acquire); }
void unpin(Obj* o) { if (atomic_fetch_sub_explicit(&o->refcount, 1, memory_order_release) == 1) retire(o); }

void retire(Obj* o) { add_to_retire_list(o, current_thread); if (should_advance_epoch()) scan_and_free(o); }
void* get(Obj* o) { pin(o); /* access */ }
```

